The paper deals with the problem of finding a path through a planar graph that closely matches a given polygonal curve, which is a problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the complexities of variations of the problem, which involves algorithms and data structures, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) another likely sub-category. The use of discrete Fr\'echet distance and the analysis of its complexities suggest that cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is also a possible sub-category. The problem of map matching involves graph theory, making cs.GR (Graph Theory) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the NP-completeness of some variations of the problem, which suggests that cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is also a possible sub-category.
